com.yubico.jaas.impl

Class YubikeyToUserMapImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yubico.jaas.impl.YubikeyToUserMapImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    YubikeyToUserMap

    public class YubikeyToUserMapImpl
extends Object
implements YubikeyToUserMap
    Class to verify that a user is the rightful user of a YubiKey. The current implementation is very rudimentary and uses a plain text file as a backend, expecting lines like "yk.vvcccfhcb.user = alice". If "bob" tries to authenticate with YubiKey "vvcccfhcb" he should be denied. There is also support for auto provisioning (default: false). If the option auto_provision_owner is set to "true", a user logging in without a prior YubiKey association will have the YubiKey they are using associated with them. This should probably only be used during an initial time window when YubiKey tokens are distributed to users, after which the auto provisioning should be turned off again.
    Author:
    Fredrik Thulin
